.SH NAME
HTMLTableCellElement.colSpan \- HTMLTableCellElement: colSpan property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]colSpan\f[B]\f[R] read\-only property of the
\f[CR]HTMLTableCellElement\f[R] interface represents the number of
columns this cell must span; this lets the cell occupy space across
multiple columns of the table.
It reflects the \f[CR]colspan\f[R] attribute.
.SH VALUE
A positive number representing the number of columns.
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] When setting a new value, the value is \f[I]clamped\f[R]
to the nearest strictly positive number.
.RE
.SH EXAMPLES
This example provides two buttons to modify the column span of the first
cell of the body.
